cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

This paper is about using a GAN for data augmentation to balance imbalanced datasets for image classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses a generative model, which falls under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves image generation, which can be categorized under cs.GR (Graphics).
